We have decided to split out the change request from the validation for several reasons. First, a validation can only be linked to a single section. By splitting it out, we can select the relevant sections rather than relying on free-form text. This will ensure that the change request is visible on all relevant sections, and not just the one it was requested on. Second, by tagging all relevant sections in the change request, we can remove those sections from the list of pending validation. Otherwise, for example, if you perform a validation on one section to determine that a grouping is necessary and are grouping 3 sections, then those other 2 sections still need to complete a validation. This allows for it to be tracked much easier. Third, there may be different change requests in the future, such as renaming a RegGroup which is in turn the Section Name. This allows us to incorporate new types of change requests in the future more easily.
